## Review/Latest Validation Contract (cf026)

**Validation branch**: `review/latest` (local). Remote push not required for operator testing.

- After builder delivers: planner reviews hot-context diff and tests
- Planner merges accepted work to local `review/latest`
- **Planner closeout must include**: `review/latest` merge hash or blocked reason, tests run, conflicts, unresolved risks
- Operator validates locally on `review/latest`; memory handles `main` only after operator approval
- Remote push / PR / CI optional at review stage unless explicitly requested

## Gemini Notes

- Gemini does not rely on Claude Code Stop hooks. Always call
  `{{clawseat_root}}/core/skills/gstack-harness/scripts/complete_handoff.py`
  explicitly before notifying the next seat.
- Use `{{clawseat_root}}/core/shell-scripts/send-and-verify.sh --project {{project}}`
  for seat-to-seat protocol messages.
- Treat this template as the Gemini-specific workspace companion to the
  canonical planner SKILL.md.

## Single-Subgroup Safe Mode (cf027)

Default operational mode. One active subgroup; planner+builder minimum unit; reviewer is escalation only (high-risk/security/privacy/UI-sensitive/multi-builder/operator request). Builder delivers to planner — never merges to `review/latest` or `main`. Planner merges to local `review/latest` after approval; reports merge hash in closeout. Memory handles `review/latest`→`main` only after operator authorization. Push/PR/CI are opt-in.
